    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"long_descriptions_container\"></div></div><div class=\"qti-layout-row\"> <div class=\"qti-layout-col12\"> <div class=\"prompt\"> <div class=\"standalone_image qti-align-center\"><img alt=\"Graph of a circle, an image, and a preimage in the x y plane with the origin labeled O. Refer to long description.\" aria-describedby=\"LDC-TLL000001_01\" src=\"/images/4d0997e73b04c2da5a7a43a53b0138ee.svg\"><div aria-label=\"Long description for circle with preimage and image in the coordinate plane\" class=\"sr-only qti-visually-hidden\" id=\"LDC-TLL000001_01\" role=\"region\"><ul>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">Neither axis has a scale or tick marks.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">A circle is graphed with its center at the origin.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">A star with five points is shown outside the circle, with two points of the star touching the circle. The star is just above the x axis and labeled Preimage.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">A segment extends from the lower point of the star that intersects the circle to the origin.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">Another star with five points, congruent to the other star, is shown outside the circle, with two points touching the circle. The star is just to the right of the y axis and labeled Image.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">A segment extends from the right point of the star that intersects the circle to the origin.</li>\n<li class=\"dap_body\">The angle between the two segments from the stars to the origin has a measure labeled pi over 3.</li>\n</ul></div></div><p class=\"dap_body\">The figure shows the preimage and image of a linear transformation&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\"><mi>L</mi></math></span>. The linear transformation function&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"L\"><math alttext=\"L\"><mi>L</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is given by&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"L open parentheses vector v close parentheses equals A times vector v\"><math alttext=\"L open parentheses vector v close parentheses equals A times vector v\"><mi>L</mi><mfenced><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span>,&nbsp;where&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\"><mi>A</mi></math></span>&nbsp;is a&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"2 by 2\"><math alttext=\"2 by 2\"><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></math></span>&nbsp;matrix and&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"vector v\"><math alttext=\"vector v\"><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math></span>&nbsp;is a column vector. Which of the following could define&nbsp;<span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\"><mi>A</mi></math></span>&nbsp;?</p> </div> </div> </div>\n",
